CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 1, 1958, pg. A14 reads: "Beltzhoover Diablos - Members of the Diablos Club of Beltzhover [sic] celebrated their second anniversary with a dinner honoring their mothers at the home of Mrs. Sara Grier on Ashdale St. Seated, left to right: The hostess, Mrs. Grier; Mmes. Myrtle Baines, Doris Patton, Geneva Martin, Bertha Simons and Nettie Wilson.  Standing: Marvella Baines, Joanne Burleigh, Ann Martin, Mrs. Charlotte Raiford, sponsor; Barbara Brown, Mary Louise Boyce, Patricia Simon, Janice Wilson, president, and Janis Grier.-Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Diablos Club members, seated, left to right: Sara Grier, Myrtle Baines, Doris Patton, Geneva Martin, Bertha Simons and Nettie Wilson; standing: Marvella Baines, Joanne Burleigh, Ann Martin, Charlotte Raiford, Barbara Brown, Mary Louise Boyce, Patricia Simon, Janice Wilson, and Janis Grier, posed behind cake for second anniversary, in home of Sara Grier, Ashdale Street, another version
